      "side": 1,
      "message": "So in icu 59 and later this takes a UChar* and UChar is defined to be char16_t (it is not supposed to be configurable anymore). At at least icu 62 and later getBuffer returns char16_t*, which is by definition the same as UChar. Except ICU waffled and still allows setting UCHAR_TYPE for transitioning applications (like Chromium) but didn\u0027t keep the discipline of using UChar everywhere.\n\nTechnically this cast invokes undefined behavior in Chromium since char16_t and uint16_t/wchar_t aren\u0027t related types. If it gets through the UBSAN bots I suppose I don\u0027t care that much since everything should work fine with \u0027real\u0027 icu (for which this is not necessary) as opposed to \u0027hacky\u0027 icu.",
